  "prompt": "What sort of a smoker was Audrey Hepburn?",
  "response": "Audrey Hepburn was known to be a moderate smoker, particularly in her later years. Smoking was relatively common among celebrities in the mid-20th century, and Hepburn was no exception. She often smoked cigarettes, though she was not typically associated with heavy or excessive smoking like some of her contemporaries. \n\nHepburn\u2019s elegant image and her advocacy for health and well-being later in life (as a UNICEF ambassador) stand in contrast to her smoking habits, which were likely influenced by the cultural norms of her time. She was eventually diagnosed with appendiceal cancer, though there is no direct evidence linking her smoking to her illness. Hepburn passed away in 1993 at the age of 63.",
